@FaceClaimer - No, [Essence Backlash](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Essence Backlash) only counters spells and the token that is created from this card is done so through an ability and not a spell. However, you might want to check out Essence Backlash's namesake, [Backlash](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Backlash). (Also see: [Delirium](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Delirium))   

In my playgroup Backlash and Delerium are both very common spells, so when someone wants to play this or [Serra Avatar](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Serra Avatar) or some other ridiculously large creature they always need to check which players are using black and red and think hard about that decision, otherwise they can end up dead very, very quickly.  

As for Ajani, as others have said the middle ability is the main attraction here. I have always overlooked this guy in the past because the other two abilities are kind of underwhelming to me, but now that I'm sitting here giving him some real thought that low costed middle ability and 4 starting loyalty are starting to look pretty attractive. Too bad I ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)
